The paper discusses the modeling and analysis of dynamic social networks, which falls under the category of social networks analysis. The paper also mentions the use of mathematical models, complex networks theory, and multi-agent systems, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.MA (multi-agent systems), cs.SY (systems and control), cs.SOC (computational social science), and cs.CYBER (cybersecurity). However, since the paper focuses more on the modeling and analysis of social dynamics, cs.SI and cs.MA are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.SOC, and cs.CYBER.
